{"type":"text","timestamp":1777219244088,"sessionID":"ses_2357b152affeevaV8Jddy0R60P","part":{"id":"prt_dca854778001oXAZPOrXS42Qja","messageID":"msg_dca84f018001ZGbPLmdFDjndgo","sessionID":"ses_2357b152affeevaV8Jddy0R60P","type":"text","text":"## Ablation Suite: Event Sourcing vs Traditional CRUD — Order Management System\n\n### 1. Consistency\n\n| | **Event Sourcing** | **Traditional CRUD** |\n|---|---|---|\n| Model | Strong eventual; event log is source of truth | Strong ACID; current state is truth |\n| Tradeoff | Read models may lag behind writes → stale reads | No projection lag, but lost history |\n| Verdict | **Lose** for OMS. Inventory/status can't tolerate stale reads. | **Win** |\n\n### 2. Query Performance\n\n| | **Event Sourcing** | **Traditional CRUD** |\n|---|---|---|\n| Reads | Fast pre-built projections (CQRS) | Fast indexed queries on live state |\n| Ad-hoc | Painful — replay or build new projection | Trivial — any SQL/ORM query |\n| Verdict | **Lose** for OMS. Ad-hoc operational queries (\"show me all delayed orders with payment issues\") are daily bread. | **Win** |\n\n### 3. Learning Curve\n\n| | **Event Sourcing** | **Traditional CRUD** |\n|---|---|---|\n| Concepts | DDD, aggregates, event versioning, CQRS, snapshots, eventual consistency | Standard ORM, well-known patterns |\n| Hiring | Niche expertise, expensive | Abundant talent, low ramp-up |\n| Verdict | **Lose** — 10x cognitive overhead for marginal benefit in this domain. | **Win** |\n\n### 4. Scalability\n\n| | **Event Sourcing** | **Traditional CRUD** |\n|---|---|---|\n| Writes | Append-only, no contention — excellent | Write contention on hot aggregates possible |\n| Reads | Read models scale independently | Read replicas work for most OMS loads |\n| Verdict | **Win**, but OMS rarely hits scale where this matters. | **Tie** (sufficient for typical OMS) |\n\n### 5. Operational Cost\n\n| | **Event Sourcing** | **Traditional CRUD** |\n|---|---|---|\n| Infrastructure | Event store + projection DB(s) + message bus | Single RDBMS |\n| Ongoing pain | Event versioning, snapshot management, projection rebuilds, replay timeouts, duplicate detection | Standard backups, monitoring |\n| Verdict | **Lose** — significantly higher TCO. | **Win** |\n\n---\n\n### ⚖️ Scorecard\nCRUD wins on 4/5 dimensions; event sourcing wins **only** on scalability (and narrowly for this domain).\n\n---\n\n### 🏆 Recommendation: **Traditional CRUD** (confidence: **85%**)\n\nOrder management is a **state-driven domain**. You care about \"what is the order's status right now?\", not \"what was its history?\". CRUD aligns naturally, keeps operations simple, and avoids projection lag, event versioning nightmares, and an oversized infrastructure bill.\n\n**The one caveat**: if you need a **complete auditable event log** (compliance, financial reconciliation), add an append-only audit table beside your CRUD — don't reach for full event sourcing. That gives you the audit trail without the CQRS/projection complexity.","time":{"start":1777219244087,"end":1777219244087}}}
